Clearer and more intense even than really experienced.
The intensity of this experience transcends the horizon of our other worldly experiences, says psychiatrist Schmidt-Degenhard.
Ultimately, oneiroids, psychosis, hallucinations and drug rush show how fragile our inner images of external reality are even in waking.
